<DOC><DOCNO> AP891124-0029 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-11-24-89 0316EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-BRF--Zambia-Unrest     11-24 0111</FIRST><SECOND>PM-BRF--Zambia-Unrest,0113</SECOND><HEAD>University Closed After Student Unrest</HEAD><DATELINE>LUSAKA, Zambia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Education authorities moving to stem threedays of student unrest have ordered all students at the capital'sonly university to leave campus today.   During protests beginning Tuesday, hundreds of studentsdemanding larger food allowances smashed their way into storeroomsto steal meat, fruit and vegetables. More than 3,000 studentsboycotted classes Tuesday.   An official circular distributed Thursday ordered all 6,000students to leave the campus in suburban Lusaka today.   The circular said student protests had disrupted studies, andauthorities decided to close down the campus two weeks ahead ofChristmas vacation. Normal studies will resume Jan. 2, it said.</TEXT></DOC>